I'm seeing it as well, but only with the SDK download wtp-sdk-I-I200605251453-200605251453.zip, not with wtp-I-I200605251453-200605251453.zip.
This is a packaging issue. If you take a look at the server.core jar file, the .class files are being place under the @dot/... directory, which is wrong.
changing component to releng and I'll investigate the fix.
just changing title to be accurate.

Fixed in I200605260305    Fri, 26 May 2006 -- 03:05 (UTC)  


I think there's a couple of issues to address in build setup. As our 
larger sdk versions (wst and jst) are created from the lower level sdk features
(common, server, xml, etc.) we should be able to build wst sdk, by _only_ common sdk, server sdk, xml sdk, etc.) but ... I had to add "includes wst" to get PDE to package things correctly. I should say, I had to "add back", as I had removed it thinking it redundant. 

This might best be solved by having our build components in releng.builder match our build components in feature defintions. 
Deserves investigation. 

The goal, is to make modular, component oriented builds, little duplicate processing, correct relationships specified in 'includes' and 'requires' to 
avoid duplicate downloads.
